		<table width="90%" bgcolor="" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-left-width:1; border-right-width: 1; border-top-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-top-width: 1; border-bottom-width: 1" bordercolor="#FFFFFF" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" ID="Table2">  
		<tr>
			<td align="left" valign="top" background="/images/necrotableheader2.gif">
				<font width="100%" face="verdana" size="1" color=white><b>Howling Stones zone-in</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="#ffebdc">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="verdana" size="1" color=white>
				written by <b>iranicus</b> on <b>3/12/2003 8:35:59 AM</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="#37437B">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="verdana" size="1" color=white><blockquote><br>
				Zone: Howling Stones (Charsis)<br>Levels: 54-60<br>Risks: High<br>Loot: Crap<br>XP: Very good<br><br>Howling Stones is a keyed zone. To get to HS the easiest way is to get the Overthere Book from Plain of Knowledge. The drop  in spot to the halls that take you to HS is at 0,1000. Some preparation before you drop down:<br>- have DMF on<br>- be full mana, full HP<br>- the scorpions in the pit do not see invis, so be invisible<br>- load up Charm (Thrall of Bones or Beguile), a fast root, ST<br>- SoW never hurts.<br><br>Now drop down the pit, run through the halls and click on the red orb to zone in (the ingame cartography system can help you to find the entrance). As soon as you zone in, FD. The zone in consists of a suspended platform, with 4 pillars in each corner and with stairs to the 4 "Wings" of HS at N, S, E and W. The E stairs are false. Under the platform is the basement, full with mobs. You wont aggro them since you are too high. On top of each stairs there are 2 golems. On the center space, pathing on the ledge beyond the pillars, there are 2 roamers. They do not path in the middle (where you are when you zone in) but they WILL aggro you if they are not in the corners. If you FD fast enough, you will be safe tho.<br><br>There is a very big chance that at least one of the 2 roamers is an undead. To break in, wait in 3rd person view until they are stopped in a corner. Stand, Charm one and sick it on the other one. Root/snare the mob, target your pet and move on the opposite side of the platform. As long as you dont step on the stairs, you wont aggro the golems. Pathing here is quite nice because when a mob tries to get to you it will allways take the path beyond the pillars as long as you take it too. This, coupled with the fact that you can easily DMF from one side to the other of the platform can easily give you time to land a root/ST then recharm. <br><br>Once the first roamer is dead, start a timer. The whole zone in is on a 21 minute timer. Invis, root and kill your pet also. Now you have the 8 golems. Leave the east golems for last. What you do now is root dot. Starting with level 57 you can single pull the golems. If you are lower, you might need need to snare/FD split. To pull them you need to stand on the opposite side of the plaform from them. Pull with snare, root, dot. If snare is resisted, just round around the pillars, re-root and snare again. They have around 5000 HPs. Epic helps a lot, you can cook 2 at a time. But it is not necessary. <br><br>East wing is special because there is a roamer that comes through the door every now and then. That roamer is high level and it summons. 90% of the times it is a undertaker skeleton, his HT hurts. You dont want him, not until you get really comfortable with the zone. If you kill the other 6 golems and have time to do east also, then wait for the roamer to leave before atempting the pull the golems. <br><br>When all golems are dead, or your timer goes off, wait for the 2 roamers to pop. You can wait invis on one of the stairs, so they wont aggro you when they pop. Rinse and repeat.<br><br>What do you do when shit hits the fan ? Because it will. Have DMF ALLWAYS on. When shit hits the fan, just jump over the edge and gate while floating down. You fall slow enough and the pit is deep enough that you will gate before the mobs in there aggro you. <br><br>Now some facts, tips:<br>- Sepulcher Skeletons are SKs, they HT for about 400 or so. Manaskin/Steel skin helps.<br>- Nothing from the mobs you want to kill summon. That include the 2 roamers and the 8 golems.<br>- Be prepared to die a few times.<br>&nbsp;<br>
			</td>
		</tr>
